<HEADLINE>
<P>
NBA; SUNS EXTEND THEIR HEAT STREAK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kevin Johnson, who had 29 points, broke Phoenix's cold spell with a 20-foot 
jumper late in the game, and the Suns continued their mastery of the Miami Heat 
with a 119-107 victory Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
 Phoenix, the only NBA team Miami hasn't beaten, improved to 15-0 in the 
series. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson's shot from the top of the key with 2:29 left ended an 8-0 Miami run 
and gave Phoenix a 109-105 lead. He later made six free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Rookie Wesley Person, who scored four points Friday night when Sacramento 
defeated the Suns 107-89, hit seven of 11 shots and finished with 23 points. 
Dan Majerle had 20 points and a career-high 15 rebounds for the Suns. 
</P>
<P>
 Glen Rice scored 23 points for the Heat. 
</P>
</TEXT>
