<HEADLINE>
<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; AGASSI NO. 2 AFTER PARIS VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Andre Agassi won the $2.2-million Paris Open on Sunday with a 6-3, 6-3, 4-6, 
7-5 victory over Marc Rosset of Switzerland and moved to No. 2 in the world 
rankings. 
</P>
<P>
 "The best thing is to win Grand Slam tournaments," said Agassi, the 1992 
Wimbledon and 1994 U.S. Open champion."Hopefully, some day you can say, 'Yeah, 
I was No. 1 for a while or for this long.' But to win the Grand Slam 
tournaments is what is most important to me." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Katarina Maleeva of Bulgaria won her first tournament in three years when she 
defeated Brenda Schultz of the Netherlands, 6-3, 6-3, in the final of the Bell 
Challenge in Quebec City. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Alberto Berasategui of Spain defeated countryman Francisco Clavet, 6-4, 6-0, 
to win the Topper Open in Montevideo, Uruguay. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 USC's Brett Hansen defeated Roger Pettersson of Nevada Las Vegas, 2-6, 6-3, 
6-1, for the championship of the Rolex-ITA Regional at UC Irvine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
