SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA VOICES / A FORUM FOR COMMUNITY ISSUES: RELIGION AND 
POLITICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is to reply to the Oct. 17 Platform "Should a Political Spouse's Beliefs 
Be Considered When Voting?" 
</P>
<P>
 I am in no way responsible for the beliefs of my husband. My husband is in no 
way responsible for my beliefs. 
</P>
<P>
 It is fair to hold Rep. Michael Huffington responsible for his wife's beliefs. 
She states she is a member of the Greek Orthodox Church. Do you have any proof 
to the contrary? 
</P>
<P>
 Should you be looking into her religion at all? Is there a religious test for 
political office, for the person running or for members of his family? 
</P>
<P>
 KAY DOWNEY 
</P>
<P>
 La Mirada 
</P>
