<TEXT>
<P>
 A gunman who fled with a hostage from a hair salon robbery in Walnut Park was 
shot to death by Los Angeles County sheriff's deputies Saturday night, 
authorities said. The woman hostage escaped and was not injured. 
</P>
<P>
 Alerted that four women were being held at gunpoint inside, deputies arrived 
at the shop, located at 7848 Pacific Blvd., shortly before 8 p.m., said Deputy 
Diane Hecht. Taking along one woman hostage with a gun pointed to her head, the 
gunman managed to drive his car about a quarter of a mile as deputies fired at 
its tires. 
</P>
<P>
 After the gunman's car crashed into a fence, the woman escaped, Hecht said. 
The 27-year-old gunman -- whose identity was being withheld pending 
notification of his family -- was shot to death by deputies, she said. 
