<P>
RAIDERS WANT ESPN RETRACTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Raiders are demanding a retraction from ESPN for its report that Coach Art 
Shell used a racist remark in a sideline argument with quarterback Jeff 
Hostetler at Miami on Oct. 16. 
</P>
<P>
 "The Raider organization and Coach Art Shell are greatly disturbed," said Amy 
Trask, who handles legal affairs for the club, "and we have demanded a 
retraction as we are entitled to under the law." 
</P>
<P>
 Copies of the letter were sent to ESPN, Capital Cities, the parent company, 
and ABC, another Capital Cities property. An ESPN spokesman confirmed receiving 
the letter but refused further comment. 
</P>
<P>
 Two days after the ESPN report, The Times reported that three independent 
sources verified that Shell derisively compared Hostetler to former Raider 
quarterback Jay Schroeder. STEVE SPRINGER 
</P>
