<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: STUDENTS ILLUSTRATE TRANSIT ALTERNATIVES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Although too young to drive, many Ventura County youths are very concerned 
about traffic and smog from cars. 
</P>
<P>
 That's the conclusion reached by the Ventura County Transportation Commission 
after receiving more than 2,500 entries in its annual contest asking students 
to illustrate "A Better Way to Go the Distance." 
</P>
<P>
 An array of colorful entries reviewed by the commission show commuters 
skating, jogging or taking the bus to work. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners received new bicycles donated by a local shop. 
</P>
<P>
 The top entries will be featured in a 1995 calendar. 
</P>
<P>
 To order a copy, call the commission at 654-2888. 
</P>
<P>
 The first-place winners are kindergarten: Heather Wilson, First Lutheran 
School, Camarillo; first grade: Nicole Casey, Santa Clara School, Santa Paula; 
second grade: Eileen Kwan, Hollow Hills School, Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Third grade: Amber Durrell, Sacred Heart School, Ventura; fourth grade: 
Jeffrey Gluck, Cornerstone Christian School, Camarillo; fifth grade: Kristin 
Van Fleet, Madera School, Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Sixth grade: Sara Lady, Chaparral Middle School, Moorpark; seventh grade: 
Patrick Dillon, Anacapa Middle School, Ventura; high school: Donovan Wheaton, 
Channel Islands High School. SARA CATANIA 
</P>
</TEXT>
