<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA MONICAS; EVENT TO MARK PARK MILESTONES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BARBARA MURPHY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Completion of another link in the Backbone Trail and the 16th anniversary of 
the Santa Monica Mountains National Recreation Area will be celebrated with a 
ceremony Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The public is invited to the 10 a.m. celebration, sponsored by the Mountains 
Conservancy Foundation and the Santa Monica Mountain Trails Council.The event 
will take place at the Tunnel 1 pullout on Kanan Road. 
</P>
<P>
 In the past year, the National Park Service has acquired eight properties 
totaling 120 acres along the Backbone Trail corridor, said David E. Gackenbach, 
recreation area superintendent. 
</P>
<P>
 About 13 miles of trail remain to be acquired or built from Kanan Road west to 
Circle X Ranch. 
</P>
<P>
 Elected officials, park agency representatives, trail advocates and hikers 
will be present at the celebration. BARBARA MURPHY 
</P>
</TEXT>
