<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It might not have the same sense of history as the Berlin Wall or the Great 
Wall of China. 
</P>
<P>
 But to Rossmoor residents, a 1 1/2-mile red brick wall that surrounds their 
community is special. 
</P>
<P>
 In recent years, the 36-year-old wall has fallen on hard times. A section of 
the wall collapsed during a 1992 earthquake. Other portions are in danger of 
toppling as well. 
</P>
<P>
 On Tuesday, Rossmoor voters are being asked to put their money where their 
heart is. Measure K and Measure L would authorize the Rossmoor Community 
Services District to maintain the wall and charge property owners $1.25 a month 
in a special tax to pay for the upkeep. Today 
</P>
<P>
 A sports memorabilia auction for the Make-A-Wish Foundation featuring 
autographed jerseys, balls, hockey sticks and pucks begins at 6 p.m. at Legends 
Sports Bar & Restaurant in Costa Mesa. 
</P>
<P>
 The auction will take place during the "Monday Night Football" game. All 
proceeds will be donated to the Make-A-Wish Foundation of Orange County, which 
grants the wishes of children suffering from terminal or life-threatening 
illnesses. Information: (714) 476-9474. 
</P>
</TEXT>
