<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; DONATED TOYS SOUGHT FOR HOLIDAY BENEFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Pacifica High School senior class is seeking donated toys for its annual 
"adopt-a-child" program benefiting local elementary school children. 
</P>
<P>
 The toy drive, which begins today, will run through Thursday.Toys should be 
unwrapped, cost no more than $5 and be intended for a child between the ages of 
5 and 8, said school district spokesman Alan Trudell. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the "adopt-a-child" program, kindergarten and disabled students from 
Clinton-Mendenhall Elementary School are invited to a holiday party thrown by 
the Pacifica senior class. This year, the event will be Dec. 14, Trudell said. 
</P>
<P>
 Donations may be dropped off on weekdays from 7 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. at the 
school's attendance office, 6851 Lampson Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 663-6515. JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
