<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAMS 27, DENVER BRONCOS 21; RAM REVIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First Quarter: Fans entering Anaheim Stadium Sunday were given Pro Bowl 
ballots and advised they were eligible to win a free trip to Honolulu for the 
game. Odds of winning were not specified, but even at one-in-million it beats 
Wayne Gandy's chances of being there. . . . Chris Chandler, who replaced a 
groggy Chris Miller as starting quarterback, is on the Pro Bowl ballot. Miller 
isn't. Huh? Ram PR spokesman said it was team's decision to forward just 
Chandler's name; that's right, there was never any truth to those reports that 
Chuck Knox wanted Chandler as his starter the rest of the year. . . . Wide 
receiver Todd Kinchen leaves line of scrimmage early, gets penalized, comes 
back on next play for 43-yard reception. This is known as the Kancatch 
Redemption. . . . Weren't they still playing baseball the last time Jerome 
Bettis scored a TD. . . . Chandler runs draw for 22 yards; Ground Chuck says, 
"That's my guy." . . . Rams 7, Broncos 0. 
</P>
<P>
 Second Quarter: Howard Griffith catches TD pass. He plays for the Rams. . . . 
Chris Chandler is outplaying John Elway. J.T. Snow hit better than Don 
Mattingly -- for a month. . . . Bettis fumbles; one more and Howard gets the 
ball. . . . Denver has only 60 yards in offense -- is Tommy Maddox stealing 
their signals? . . . Elway throws misguided pass, gets lucky because it hits 
Anthony Newman in his hands, falls incomplete. . . . Contestants for Punt, Pack 
& Move contest at halftime make their way to field. . . . Rams 17, Broncos 3. 
</P>
<P>
 Third Quarter: Chandler runs QB sneak, gets concussion, then throws 30-yard TD 
pass to Flipper Anderson. Claims later he knew what he was doing. . . . Elway 
now has Rams just where he wants them -- up by 21 points. . . . Miller's not 
sure where he is, but he goes in for a woozy Chandler. What does that tell you 
about Maddox? . . . George Foreman wins heavyweight championship at age 45; 
Gandy starts eating cheeseburgers. . . . Chandler has now thrown for 223 yards, 
making New Orleans' linebacker Ernest Dixon Ram MVP for knocking Miller out. . 
. . Elway won't have to worry about losing another Super Bowl this year. . . . 
Rams 24, Broncos 6. 
</P>
<P>
 Fourth Quarter: Wymon Henderson enters game, Broncos begin comeback. . . . 
Glyn Millburn is wide open, scores, must have been Wymon's guy. . . . Derek 
Russell scores TD, must have been Wymon's guy. . . . Shannon Sharpe catches 
two-point conversion and just where was Wymon? . . . Ram reverse sprung by 
Chandler block. Ground Chuck smiles, "That's my guy." . . . Bettis stopped 
three straight times at goal line, Drayton has tantrum, Knox has excuse to omit 
him from game plan next week. . . . Surprise, surprise, Elway throws to Wymon's 
guy on fourth down, Wymon's guy tries diving catch, can't. So what did you 
expect? . . . Rams 27, Broncos 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Game Summary: St. Louis, Baltimore, Oakland? Rams (4-5) versus Raiders (4-5). 
Loser leaves town. 
</P>
</TEXT>
