<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; MICHEL'S HAT TRICK IN SECOND HALF LIFTS UCI IN WATER POLO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jean Michel scored three second-half goals to help UC Irvine, the 
eighth-ranked team in the nation, to an 8-5 water polo victory over 
fifth-ranked UCLA in a Mountain Pacific Sports Federation game Sunday at UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA (13-10, 2-6) led, 3-0, early in the second quarter before Irvine (8-11, 
3-5) rallied to tie it with the help of a two-point goal by Omar Amr in the 
final minute of the half. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine outscored UCLA, 3-2, in the third quarter and, 2-0, in the fourth. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Rolex-ITA Southern California men's regional: 
</P>
<P>
 Hansen wins singles title -- Brett Hansen, a former UCI player currently at 
USC, won the singles title with a 2-6, 6-3, 6-1 victory over Roger Pettersson 
of Nevada Las Vegas. Pettersson is ranked 13th and Hansen 39th in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
 The doubles final involved two teams from Pepperdine. Simon Aspelin and Troy 
Budgen beat Chris Hill and Mike Jessup, 6-2, 7-6. Aspelin and Budgen are ranked 
sixth in the nation. 
</P>
<P>
 In nonconference women's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Hawaii 2, CS Fullerton 1 -- Nicki Arakawa was credited with a goal that went 
off a Cal State Fullerton player then into the Titans' goal to break a 1-1 tie 
in the 76th minute. Michelle Rice had tied it three minutes earlier for the 
Titans (6-9-2). 
</P>
<P>
 In the Long Beach State round-robin water polo tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State splits two -- The 49ers lost to 10th-ranked Air Force, 11-8, 
but came back to beat Loyola Marymount, 14-10. 
</P>
<P>
 Tim Ault and Tim Finley had three goals each on the loss to Air Force. Long 
Beach (5-15) opened a 3-0 lead at the end of the first quarter and the teams. 
Long Beach led, 7-3, with four minutes left in the third quarter but were 
outscored, 8-1, the rest of the way. 
</P>
<P>
 Ian Taylor and Finley had five goals each in the victory over Loyola Marymount 
(17-12). Air Force (13-8) also beat Loyola Marymount, 14-9. 
</P>
</TEXT>
