<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRVINE'S TRI-LITE WINS $3.4-MILLION CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tri-Lite Inc. said Friday that its Prolite unit has won a $3.4-million 
contract to install lighting systems at the University of Maryland's campus in 
College Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The Irvine-based lighting equipment manufacturer will install new fixtures 
made by two Tri-Lite subsidiaries, SPL Corp. and NL Corp. 
</P>
<P>
 Company President Alvin Katz said the energy-efficient equipment will save the 
university $1 million a year in electricity costs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
